Feyisayo Popoola Wapic Insurance Plc has announced the extension of the offer period for its rights issue. The company had in November opened subscription to its rights issue, where it offered 15,613,194,623 ordinary shares of 50 kobo each at 38 kobo per share. It said the rights issue was on the basis of seven new ordinary shares for every six ordinary shares held as of the close of business on September 19, 2019. Wapic said it aimed to raise N5.93bn to enable it to invest in Wapic Life Assurance Limited to meet regulatory capital requirements and invest in Wapic Insurance (Ghana) Limited. The Nigerian Stock Exchange said in a notice on Tuesday that further to the market bulletin of November 20, 2019, wherein the market was notified of the offer period for the rights issue of Wapic Insurance, the Securities and Exchange Commission had approved a further extension of the offer period. It said with SECâ€™s approval, the offer, which was initially scheduled to close on Tuesday, December 31, 2019, would now close on Friday, January 10, 2020. CopyrightPUNCH.
